      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I had an idea similar to this in my Content Raiding Server idea, and 1.0 epics are required to finish luclin and enter PoP (among other things).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The other quests are&amp;nbsp;VP key to enter Velious,&amp;nbsp;ST key&amp;nbsp;to enter Luclin,&amp;nbsp;VT key (and 1.0 epic)&amp;nbsp;to enter PoP, Time key to enter Gates, Qvic flag to enter OoW ect. Those are all required on each character who wants to advance.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;In addition, the final raid target of each expansion must be killed to unlock the next expansion serverwide. CT to open Kunark, Phara Dar to open Velious, wake Sleeper and kill Vulak to open Luclin, kill Seru and Aten to open PoP, kill Quarm to open Gates.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;You could add some quests to be completed once&amp;nbsp;also for serverwide unlocking. Such as BiC and other involved quests. The PoP one that requires the part from each EP god, the 10th Dain ring, and so on.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It would slow down the top guild, prevent it from advancing too far beyond the general population, and more people would enjoy the game if they had to get keys for old expansion to enter the next one.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
