&lt;DIV&gt;The thing is, it honeslty wouldn't.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The best guild on this server will not have a capatalist-style DKP system where people bid on quest pieces: the raid leader will have enough forsight to realize that since they're abandoning content pretty much as soon as they defeat it with the exception of a very few farm stages, enough quest pieces will only drop to give a few people quests.&amp;nbsp; They will award those pieces all to the same person.&amp;nbsp; There are obvious exceptions: each cleric in the guild will have their epic.&amp;nbsp; But, overall, one necromancer, probably the one who spends the most time online, will be given all of his hard planes-drops, since the planes won't be done enough time for 2+ necros to get their epic.&amp;nbsp; At lest one epic quest / class (except maybe Beastlord) will be completed WELL before PoP... they will probably be completed before Luclin, perhaps even before velious.&amp;nbsp; The same goes for other quests.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;8th coldain shawl?&amp;nbsp; As soon as velious hits, that's going to be my primary goal.&amp;nbsp; I guarantee I'll have it done within a month, maybe less (tradeskills will be where they need to be before the fall of Phara Dar).&amp;nbsp; It's&amp;nbsp;my favorite content hands down, and I'm going to have a lot of fun doing it.&amp;nbsp; Someone I'm sure feels the same way about the 10 rings.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The elemental planes god quest?&amp;nbsp; As I said, that quest will all be awarded to the same person (like difficult to complete epics), and so is unlikely to hold back progression (at most you're talking 2-3 extra raids, TOPS, and that could be in only half a week).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
